   <title>Dos and Don’ts</title>
   <sect2 id="ch0017s0007s01" role="Heading">
      <title>Dos</title>
      <itemizedlist role="UnorderedListMarkBullet">
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Supplement a categorical diagnosis with a dimensional assessment of frequency and degree of substance use, patterns within specific drug classes, and impairment.</para>
         </listitem>
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Assess for co-occurring mental health symptoms.</para>
         </listitem>
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Consider<emphasis>how</emphasis> co-occurring symptoms may be contributing to an SUD.</para>
         </listitem>
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Elicit the client’s treatment goals.</para>
         </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
   </sect2>
   <sect2 id="ch0017s0007s02" role="Heading">
      <title>Don’ts</title>
      <itemizedlist role="UnorderedListMarkBullet">
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Use only a categorical diagnosis of substance use disorder.</para>
         </listitem>
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Ignore co-occurring mental health symptoms that may be a primary function of a client’s substance use.</para>
         </listitem>
         <listitem>
            <para role="Para">Fail to identify the most appropriate tools<indexterm significance="normal">
                  <primary>tools</primary>
               </indexterm>for the specific setting, client, or diagnostic purpose.</para>
         </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
   </sect2>
</sect1>